    <text>
        <body>
            <pb n="1R"/>
            <p rend="align(right)">
                <placeName>Kingston Jamaica</placeName>
            </p>
            <p rend="align(right)">
                <date>Jany. 4Th 5623=1863</date>
            </p>
            <p>High Esteeme<del>n</del>d</p>
            <p rend="indent(1)">Revd. &amp; Dear Sir!</p>
            <p rend="indent(3)">You really must <del>in</del> with your<lb/> usual kind feeling,
                pardon my not having addressed<lb/> you on this, as our mutual and esteemed friend
                    <persName>Mr. Nathan</persName><lb/> can assure you that since my arrival here,
                I have<lb/> had my time fully occupied with public as well as<lb/> private duties. I
                need not tell you of my changing<lb/> appointments, as you are already aware of the
                fact;<lb/> therefore, suffice it for me to inform you, that my<lb/>
                <del>cause</del> reason for so doing was, that the situation here offered to<lb/>
                me, was far more beneficial than the one I held in<lb/>
                <placeName>Saint Thomas</placeName>. News I have not any to write—<lb/> you have an
                excellent and worthy agent here in <persName>Mr.<lb/> Nathan</persName>, to whom I
                have just handed the name of<lb/> a new subscriber to the “Occident”— As my
                subscription<lb/> has formerly been sent through <persName>Mr. Piza</persName> of
                    <placeName>St. Thomas</placeName>,<lb/> will you kindly acquaint me as to the
                date of its<lb/> becoming due? And, I presume that you will now<lb/> send my numbers
                through <persName>Mr. N.</persName> as I received the<lb/> are forwarded by last
                mail. I read the abusive<lb/> remarks of that scurrilous sheer<add>?</add> the
                “Record” which<lb/> surely you will not feign to notice. What else but—<lb/> the
                qualification of a little low chatham is <add>?</add> &amp; indecency, can be
                extracted from such a source or</p>
            <pb n="1V"/>
            <p>company? Or, who constituted a few chatham Is clothes<lb/> boys teachers in
                    <placeName>Israel</placeName>? So the <persName>Revd. Mr.
                DeSolla</persName><lb/> is with you again, pray O<add>?</add> let him introduce<lb/>
                to your notice or community, all the <add>ממזרים</add><lb/> in the <placeName>United
                    States</placeName>, or he will make a fine affair<lb/> of the congregation. My
                respected friend <persName>Revd. L. M.<lb/> Isaacs</persName> informs me that
                    <persName>Mr. De S</persName> wished to attach<lb/>
                <persName>Mr. Morais</persName> in the messenger, but that he (<persName>Mr
                    I</persName>) refused<lb/> to permit it. No doubt it will be “recorded” in the<lb/>
                <placeName>Chatham St.</placeName> gazette. Now Revd. &amp; Dear Sir, I have<lb/> an
                important congregational matter on hand, you<lb/> must therefore pardon my brevity
                &amp; scrawl, which I<lb/> feel ashamed to send by the side of that of my
                superior.<lb/> However as he promises me his assistance I may<lb/> yet hope to some
                day climb the ladder<lb/> in the hope<lb/> that you are in perfect health. With most
                sincere<lb/> wishes to your prosperity, I now with very best regards</p>
            <p rend="indent(6)">Subscribe myself</p>
            <p rend="indent(6)">Most Sincerely Yours</p>
            <p rend="indent(7)">
                <persName role="author">M. O. I. Myers</persName>
            </p>
            <p>
                <addressee>Revd. I Leeser</addressee>
            </p>
            <p rend="indent(2)">Please let me have as <hi rend="underline">early</hi> as<lb/>
                <hi rend="underline">possible</hi> 10 copies of your <add>מורה דרך</add> Heb Primer
                No 1<lb/> and if obtainable a copy of work called <add>כפי מנהג הספרדים</add>
                published in <placeName>Amsterdam</placeName> in <date>5528</date></p>
        </body>
